    "description": "Molitec Steel Co., Ltd. processes and sells cold rolled special, stainless, and various steel strips in Japan. The company offers press worked products, including automotive and agricultural machine parts, household electrical appliances, and dies fabrication products; and heat-treated products, such as hardened and tempered steel strips for automobile-clutch parts, blades and saws, power springs, and other pressed parts. It also provides metal materials comprising special, stainless, mild steel, and precoated sheets. In addition, the company manufactures and sells machinery tools, plastic products, and steel and plastic parts. The company was formerly known as Mori&Co. and changed its name to Molitec Steel Co., Ltd. in January 1990. Molitec Steel Co., Ltd. was founded in 1943 and is headquartered in Chuo, Japan."
